}}
{{See also|2012 UCLA Bruins football team}}
[[File:UCLA vs. USC 2012.JPG|thumb|left|UCLA defeats USC 38-28 in the Rose Bowl]]
The matchup was the first time since 2005 that UCLA and USC met as ranked teams.  It was also the first time since 2001 that the Bruins entered the game ranked higher than the Trojans.<ref>{{cite news|title=Southern Cal-UCLA Preview|date=November 17, 2012|work=ESPN.com|url=http://scores.espn.go.com/ncf/preview?gameId=323220026|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6CIjX2149|archivedate=November 19, 2012|deadurl=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=The Back and the Coach Behind U.C.L.A.<U+2019>s Revival|first=Greg|last=Bishop|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/17/sports/ncaafootball/jim-l-mora-and-johnathan-franklin-lead-ucla-into-usc-game.html?ref=gregbishop&_r=0&pagewanted=all|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=November 16, 2012|accessdate=November 19, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6CIjhQ25f|archivedate=November 19, 2012}}</ref>

'''1st quarter scoring:''' UCLA <U+2013> [[Brett Hundley]] 1-yard run (Ka'i  Fairbairn kick); UCLA <U+2013> Fairbairn 23-yard field goal; UCLA <U+2013> Joseph Fauria 17-yard pass from Hundley (Fairbairn kick).
			
'''2nd quarter scoring:''' UCLA <U+2013> [[Johnathan Franklin]] 16-yard run (Fairbairn kick); USC <U+2013> Nelson Agholor 33-yard pass from Matt Barkley (Andre Heidari kick); USC <U+2013> Randall Telfer 2-yard pass from Barkley (Heidari kick). 
  	  	  	
'''3rd quarter scoring:''' USC <U+2013> George Uko 0-yard fumble recovery (Heidari kick failed); UCLA <U+2013> Hundley 3-yard run (Fairbairn kick). 
  	  	  	
'''4th quarter scoring:''' USC <U+2013> Marqise Lee 14-yard pass from Barkley (Robert Woods pass from Barkley); UCLA <U+2013> Franklin 29-yard run (Fairbairn kick).

Following the game, the Athletics Department sent out an e-mail to students that "After beating our cross-town rival, UCLA, we are the South Division Champions and will play in the 2012 Pac-12 Championship Game. Since we are the South Division representative we will be traveling to play Oregon in Eugene or Stanford in Palo Alto." to encourage students to buy tickets to the [[2012 Pacific-12 Football Championship Game]].<ref>[http://collegespun.com/national/usc-sends-email-to-students-for-pac-12-title-game-the-trojans-didnt-make USC Sends Email To Students For Pac-12 Title Game The Trojans Didn<U+2019>t Make], CollegeSpun.com, December 3, 2012</ref>
{{-}}

